1 wilcoxon-test

1.1 Wilcoxon Test

The data contains 3 files, which analyze the RNAseq gene expression data of healthy people ("Healthy"), patients with type 1 disease ("CCC"), and patients with type 2 disease ("DCM"). Gene_expression.txt is the RNAseq result. Informations_phenotypes.txt is the phenotype information, and Conversion_ID_Name.tab is the statistical data of patients or healthy people.

data <- read.table("D:/0-AMU/les cours/S1-7-STAT2-complements (DLAD)/R/DONNEES/Gene_expression.txt", sep = "\t", header = TRUE)
metadata <- read.table("D:/0-AMU/les cours/S1-7-STAT2-complements (DLAD)/R/DONNEES/Informations_phenotypes.txt", sep = "\t", header = TRUE)
metafeature <- read.table("D:/0-AMU/les cours/S1-7-STAT2-complements (DLAD)/R/DONNEES/Conversion_ID_Name.tab", sep = "\t", header = TRUE)

healthyName <- metadata$Sample[metadata$Phenotype == "Healthy"]
caseName <- metadata$Sample[metadata$Phenotype == "CCC"]

pvalueW1 <- numeric(nrow(data))

wilcoxTest <- function(x){
  test <- wilcox.test(x[healthyName], x[caseName])
  return(test$p.value)
}

pvalueW1 <- apply(data, 1, wilcoxTest)
resultsw1 <- data.frame(EnsemblID = names(pvalueW1), Pvalue = pvalueW1)
resultsw1 <- left_join(resultsw1, metafeature)

2.2 Most 5 genes among Healthy, CCC and DCM by Wilcoxon 

ID_HC <- resultsw1$EnsemblID[which(resultsw1$Pvalue <= 0.05)]
ID_HD <- resultsw2$EnsemblID[which(resultsw2$Pvalue <= 0.05)]

ID_CD <- resultsw3$EnsemblID[which(resultsw3$Pvalue <= 0.05)]

N123 <- intersect(intersect(ID_HC, ID_HD), ID_CD)
N123 <- N123[1:5]

raw_data <- data[N123,]
raw_data$Gene <- row.names(raw_data)

pheno <- c()

namesHealthy <- as.character(metadata$Sample[metadata$Phenotype == "Healthy"])
namesCCC <- as.character(metadata$Sample[metadata$Phenotype == "CCC"])
namesDCM <- as.character(metadata$Sample[metadata$Phenotype == "DCM"])


raw_data <- reshape2::melt(raw_data)

for(i in 1:nrow(raw_data)){
  if(raw_data$variable[i] %in% namesHealthy){
    pheno <- c(pheno, "Healthy")
  }
  else if(raw_data$variable[i] %in% namesDCM){
    pheno <- c(pheno, "DCM")
  }
  else{
    pheno <- c(pheno, "CCC")
  }
}

raw_data$Phenotype <- pheno
p <- ggplot(raw_data, aes(x = Gene, y = value, fill = Phenotype)) +
  geom_boxplot() + 
  xlab("Gene ID") + 
  ylab("Gene expression") + 
  ggtitle("Most 5 genes among Healthy, CCC and DCM by Wilcoxon") + 
  theme_classic() + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 5))
  
plot(p)

2.3 Correlation test

namesCCC <- as.character(metadata$Sample[metadata$Phenotype == "CCC"])
namesDCM <- as.character(metadata$Sample[metadata$Phenotype == "DCM"])
N12 <- intersect(ID_HC, ID_HD)
Diff <- data.frame(data[N12, c(namesCCC, namesDCM)])

corrtest <- function(x){
    test <- cor(
      x[namesCCC],
      x[namesDCM],
      method = "pearson"
    )
    return(test)
}
TestC <- apply(Diff, 1, corrtest)
corTest <- data.frame(EnsemblID = names(TestC), R = TestC)
head(corTest)
